<item>
            <title>[LU-6778] nodemap proc files don&apos;t work for very large nodemaps</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6778</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;John Hammond pointed out that the seq_show functions that are used for the nodemaps don&apos;t iterate, and so they won&apos;t work if the output data is more than the seq_file limit. They need to be redone with large nodemaps in mind.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="30867">LU-6778</key>
            <summary>nodemap proc files don&apos;t work for very large nodemaps</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11310&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Improvement</type>
